        public boolean isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly()
        Description copied from interface: GenerationConfig
        Gets the 'constructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly' configuration option. This is a legacy configuration option used to turn on the GenerationConfig.isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor() and off the GenerationConfig.isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor() configuration options. It is specifically tied to the GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() property, and will do nothing if that property is not enabled
        Specified by:
        isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly in interface GenerationConfig
        Returns:
        false

      • isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor

        public boolean isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor()
        Description copied from interface: GenerationConfig
        Gets the 'constructorsIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with GenerationConfig.isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true. If GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is set to true then this configuration determines whether the resulting object should include a constructor with only the required properties as parameters.
        Specified by:
        isIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor in interface GenerationConfig
        Returns:
        false

      • isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor

        public boolean isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor()
        Description copied from interface: GenerationConfig
        Gets the 'constructorsIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with GenerationConfig.isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true. If GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is set to true then this configuration determines whether the resulting object should include a constructor with all listed properties as parameters.
        Specified by:
        isIncludeAllPropertiesConstructor in interface GenerationConfig
        Returns:
        true

      • isIncludeCopyConstructor

        public boolean isIncludeCopyConstructor()
        Description copied from interface: GenerationConfig
        Gets the 'constructorsIncludeRequiredPropertiesConstructor' configuration option. This property works in collaboration with the GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() configuration option and is incompatible with GenerationConfig.isConstructorsRequiredPropertiesOnly(), and will have no effect if GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is not set to true. If GenerationConfig.isIncludeConstructors() is set to true then this configuration determines whether the resulting object should include a constructor the class itself as a parameter, with the expectation that all properties from the originating class will assigned to the new class.
